						<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="/war">All a battle</a></h1>
			
					</header>
		
					<div class="entry-content">

						<p>If people act in their self interest, then it follows the natural state of things is at least fairly war like. Now, this could lead to a right wing way of thinking, <em>survival of the fittest</em> blah, blah, blah, but survival, and winning, means tactics, and that means seeking alliances, identifying people of the same stripe etc.</p>
						
						<p>Moaning about your enemy's behaviour is a waste of time. Your enemy only seeks to further her position. Doing the &#8216;right&#8217; thing is one of many battlegrounds; the war's the important thing. And to win a war you have to be prepared to fight, and see it as a war in the first place.</p>
			
